sub_title: Researcher Phd Candidate | Applied Geophysics & Petrophysics | Department of Geoscience & Engineering (GSE) |  Faculty of Civil Engineering & Geosciences | TU Delft
summary:
Experienced Electronic & Instrumentation Engineer (BSc. in Electronic Engineering) with a Master in Geophysics (Earthquake Seismology) focused on “Broadband Seismic Sensors”. With around 12 years of working in industrial automation & instrumentation for different sciences. 
Skilled in LabVIEW, control and vibration fields, instrumentation & application of sensors in the process of simulation & modeling of physical phenomenon, data logging & analyzing & software developing.  
From Dec 2022, Researcher Phd Candidate in Applied Geophysics & Petrophysics at Department of Geoscience & Engineering (GSE), Faculty of Civil Engineering & Geosciences, TU Delft.
My new challenge will be Geophysical Subsurface Railway Embankment and Soil Monitoring.
